First if $N$ is $2\times2$ matrix with $\operatorname{tr}(N)=0$, then $N^2$ is scalar (either $N$ is nilpotent or its eigenvalues are opposite and have same square). This implies that $\operatorname{tr}(N^3)=0$. And 
$$\begin{eqnarray}
(AB-BA)^3 &=& (ABABAB - BABABA) + (ABBABA + BABAAB + BAABBA) \\
 && - (ABABBA + ABBAAB + BAABAB)

\end{eqnarray}
$$ taking the trace this gives $$0 = 0 + 3\operatorname{tr}(ABBABA) - 3 \operatorname{tr}(ABABBA) = 3 \operatorname{tr}(AABBAB - AABABB).$$
